- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper mentions programs and threads as components, which are related to programming languages. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses architectures for heterogeneous collectives of components, which can be applied to distributed and parallel computing. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper mentions monoids, which are algebraic structures used in abstract algebra and can be applied to data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper mentions financial transfers, which are related to cryptography and security. However, this topic is not the main focus of the paper.
